<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06245100 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06245100 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; BASEBALL; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Bo Jackson will make his Chicago White Sox debut as designated hitter Mondaynight against his old teammates, the Kansas City Royals.;   The White Sox madethat announcement after Saturday night's 10-5 victory over the ClevelandIndians, and Jackson was ecstatic about returning to the big leagues as aplayer.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JACKSON TO RETURN MONDAYGWYNN STILL OUT WITH KNEE PROBLEM  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Baseball Notes  </MEMO><TEXT>     &quot;I'm excited,&quot; said Jackson, whose hip was injured in an NFL playoff gamelast season. &quot;I'm excited to be back. Most people said I wouldn't playbaseball again.&quot;;   Jackson spent the last week testing his hip in six gameswith White Sox minor league clubs. He met with trainer Herm Schneider, whosaid, &quot;From a medical standpoint, Bo's ready to play major league baseballagain. He's ready in terms of range, flexibility, strength, pain level andframe of mind.&quot;;   Jackson said, &quot;If I strike out four times, that's great,because I'll be back on the field doing it.;   &quot;I'll probably always walk witha limp,&quot; Jackson said, &quot;but I run better than I walk. So, expect to see me runa lot.&quot;; INJECTIONS FOR GWYNN: Tony Gwynn's left knee was drained and hereceived a cortisone shot, procedures that will keep the San Diego Padresoutfielder out of action for at least two more games.;   Dr. Jan Fronekdrained fluid from Gwynn's knee, which has been bothering him since he hurt itsliding during a game at Houston earlier this month.;   Manager Greg Riddoch,concerned with the way Gwynn was hobbling to first base, removed the rightfielder after the seventh inning of Friday's game against Pittsburgh.;   Aftertwo days, Gwynn's condition and availability will be evaluated on a day-to-daybasis.;   Saturday's game was only the second Gwynn had missed this season.After Saturday night's games, Gwynn was leading the National League inbatting, at .323.; ETC.: Pittsburgh Pirates playoff and World Series ticketswill go on sale Tuesday by mail, the team said Saturday. If the Pirates winthe N.L. East, the first two playoff games will be at Three Rivers Stadium.Games 6 and 7 also will be in Pittsburgh if necessary. If the Pirates play inthe World Series, Games 3 and 4 will be played in Pittsburgh, as will Game 5,if necessary. . . . The California Angels have purchased the contract offormer New York Mets catcher Barry Lyons, whom the Angels signed as a freeagent June 19. Lyons hit .317 in 46 games with Triple-A Edmonton.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910901  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  410  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday, September 1, 199100245100,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>